===Etymology 3===
Old Norse ''[[skal]]'', "bowl". Confer Old English ''[[scealu]]'', "cup", "shell"; Dutch ''[[schaal]]''; German ''[[Schale]]''; Old High German ''[[scala#Old High German|scala]]''; Gothic ''[[skalja]]''. Cognate with ''[[scale#Etymology 2|scale]]'', as in Etymology 2.
====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}
#A [[device]] to [[measure]] [[mass]] or [[weight]].
#:''After the long, lazy winter I was afraid to get on the '''scale'''.''
#Either of the [[pan]]s, [[tray]]s, or [[dish]]es of a [[balance]].
